# JavaScript Odyssey – A Five-World Developer Ascension

## Overview

JavaScript Odyssey is a single-page web application designed as a structured learning system that demonstrates core JavaScript concepts through five progressive modules ("Worlds").

Each world focuses on a specific area of JavaScript mastery, from basic logic to DOM manipulation.

---

## What This Project Demonstrates

- Structured problem solving
- Separation of logic and UI
- Reusable function design
- Array and object manipulation
- DOM interaction and state updates
- Clean code organization

---

## Application Structure

### World 1 – Foundations

Basic input handling and validation

- Discount Calculator
- Grade Calculator
- Password Checker

### World 2 – Logic Kingdom

Pure functions and reusable logic

- Calculator functions
- Factorial
- BMI Calculator
- Leap Year Checker

### World 3 – Array Arena

Array manipulation and iteration

- Sum & Average
- Sorting
- Filtering
- Duplicate removal

### World 4 – Object City

Object-based data modeling

- Contact Book
- Shopping Cart Simulator
- Student Object System

### World 5 – DOM Dimension

Interactive browser features

- Todo App
- Modal System
- Form Validation
- Live Counters

---

## Tech Stack

- HTML5
- CSS3
- Vanilla JavaScript (No frameworks)

---

## Key Engineering Decisions

- Logic is separated from DOM manipulation
- Modular file structure for scalability
- Reusable utility functions
- Event-driven architecture
